title: Omicron Variant Now Dominates in England and Scotland, Health Data Show
sub_head: Infections of the Covid-19 variant are estimated to be doubling in less than two days across much of England
body:
LONDONâ€”Omicron has become the dominant variant of the coronavirus in England and Scotland, according to estimates derived from British health data, demonstrating its ability to outcompete the Delta strain that currently dominates in the U.S. and other parts of the world.
The development came as the U.K. reported Friday a record number of new daily cases since the start of the pandemic: more than 93,000, compared with 88,000 Thursday. New cases have grown on average by 39% in the latest week compared with the previous seven days.
